channel.title: Help with portfowarding
channel.description: I have 2 computers the one i am using is connected to the router through an ethernet cord, the other computer has the modem and stuff connected to it, so i have an ip on the computer im using now and a different ip on the other computer(with modem connected to it). Which ip address should i put in on the portfowarding site?

item.title: Help with portfowarding
item.dc:creator: @facundo facundo
item.description:
@facundo wrote:

ok in the portfowarding space you have to put the ip that the program no-ip gives to you. then save and reboot, and your router should be portfowarded.
